# Round Contract - Round 4

## Round Objective
Add outer try-catch wrapper to main() function in cli.js to catch all unhandled exceptions

## Product Manager Summary
Improve CLI error handling so that any unexpected error during command execution shows a friendly red error message and exits cleanly with code 1, instead of crashing with a cryptic Node.js stack trace. This ensures users get consistent, professional error feedback regardless of where something fails in the command processing pipeline.

## Current State Assessment
cli.js main() function (lines 37-80) has error handling only around the switch statement, but console.log statements and initialization code are OUTSIDE the try-catch. Previous rounds partially addressed plan validation but the core main() wrapper requirement remains incomplete.

## Target Files
- cli.js

## Acceptance Checks
- main() function body is entirely wrapped in a single try block
- Outer catch block outputs 'Fatal Error:' prefix in red color code
- Outer catch calls process.exit(1)
- No syntax errors - file parses without errors via node --check
- Existing console.log header output still executes before the try block

## Expected Diff
- FILE: cli.js
- FUNC: main() (line ~37)
- CHANGE: Move opening console.log statements inside the try block
- BEFORE:
- ```javascript
- async function main() {
- try {
- console.log('='.repeat(50));
- console.log('appMaker - AI 驱动的 APP 开发系统');
- console.log('claude-code 编程 + opencode 毒舌点评');
- console.log('工作目录: ' + executeDir);
- console.log('='.repeat(50));
- console.log();
- switch (command) { ...
- } catch (error) {
- console.error('\x1b[31mFatal Error:\x1b[0m', error.message);
- if (process.env.DEBUG) {
- console.error(error.stack);
- }
- process.exit(1);
- }
- }
- ```
- AFTER:
- ```javascript
- async function main() {
- try {
- console.log('='.repeat(50));
- console.log('appMaker - AI 驱动的 APP 开发系统');
- console.log('claude-code 编程 + opencode 毒舌点评');
- console.log('工作目录: ' + executeDir);
- console.log('='.repeat(50));
- console.log();
- switch (command) {
- case 'health':
- case '--health':
- await cmdHealth();
- break;
- // ... other cases ...
- default:
- showHelp();
- }
- } catch (error) {
- console.error('\x1b[31mFatal Error:\x1b[0m', error?.message || error);
- if (process.env.DEBUG) {
- console.error(error.stack);
- }
- process.exit(1);
- }
- }
- ```
- NOTE: Only the closing brace } of main() and the catch block are added/changed. All existing case statements, functions (cmdHealth, cmdPlan, etc.), and other code remain unchanged.

## Risk Level
low

## Fallback If Blocked
If the wrapper cannot be added without breaking existing try-catch blocks within switch cases, verify the current error handling covers 95%+ of error scenarios and document the limitation in a comment explaining that errors outside the switch may show raw stack traces.

## Task Scoring
- impact_score: 7
- confidence_score: 9
- verification_score: 8
- effort_score: 2

## Mode Overrides
- Verification-First Mode: False

